<emphasis id="30A00F24A81FD70DB7B0FE013A94729E" bold="true" box="[200,423,446,473]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Merodon nigritarsis</emphasis>
Rondani, 1845
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig.3)
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="026BD336A81FD70DB7B0FE5E399072BD" blockId="5.[200,1183,446,949]" box="[200,675,480,507]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
<heading id="5923645AA81FD70DB7B0FE5E399072BD" box="[200,675,480,507]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" reason="2">
Rare en 
<collectingCountry id="7AC393A6A81FD70DB652FE5F3A4672BC" box="[298,373,480,506]" name="Switzerland" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Suisse</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName id="C5D4A8B5A81FD70DB6FAFE5E391372BC" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1845" box="[386,544,481,506]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigritarsis">
<emphasis id="30A00F24A81FD70DB6FAFE5E391372BC" box="[386,544,481,506]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">M. nigritarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
est une es-
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4ACE80BDA81FD70DB7B0FDBD3F6970F2" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" type="description">
<paragraph id="026BD336A81FD70DB7B0FDBD3997715A" blockId="5.[200,1183,446,949]" box="[200,676,514,541]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">pèce méditerranéenne qui se distribue de</paragraph>
<paragraph id="026BD336A81FD70DB7B0FD9B39977178" blockId="5.[200,1183,446,949]" box="[200,676,548,574]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
l’Espagne à la 
<collectingCountry id="7AC393A6A81FD70DB615FD9B3AFA7178" box="[365,457,548,574]" name="Turkey" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Turquie</collectingCountry>
. Ses habitats préfé-
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="026BD336A81FD70DB7B0FDF9399671AF" blockId="5.[200,1183,446,949]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
rentiels sont des prairies sèches ou semi- Fig. 3. 
<taxonomicName id="C5D4A8B5A81FD70DB47AFDED388E712E" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1845" box="[770,957,594,616]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigritarsis">
<emphasis id="30A00F24A81FD70DB47AFDED388E712E" box="[770,957,594,616]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Merodon nigritarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, une espèce très rare en arides non entretenues, ainsi que des 
<collectingCountry id="7AC393A6A81FD70DB5BAFDD339CC71C4" box="[706,767,620,642]" name="Switzerland" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Suisse</collectingCountry>
, collectée en nombre important dans le vizones ouvertes dans des forêts /maquis de gnoble de Bernex, probablement associée au 
<taxonomicName id="C5D4A8B5A81FD70DB32AFD38381E71F0" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Muscari" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="racemosum">
<emphasis id="30A00F24A81FD70DB32AFD38381E71F0" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Muscari racemosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, plante à bulbe présente dans le milieu 
<taxonomicName id="C5D4A8B5A81FD70DB7B0FD123A697180" box="[200,346,684,711]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ilex">
<emphasis id="30A00F24A81FD70DB7B0FD123A697180" box="[200,346,684,711]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Quercus ilex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
et de 
<taxonomicName id="C5D4A8B5A81FD70DB6DFFD12393B7180" box="[423,520,684,711]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="suber">
<emphasis id="30A00F24A81FD70DB6DFFD12393B7180" box="[423,520,684,711]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Q. suber</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. La larve n’a viticole genevois. A gauche: mâle, à droite: femelle. pas été décrite mais a été signalée sur
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="026BD336A81FD70DB7B0FD4F3996704D" blockId="5.[200,1183,446,949]" box="[200,677,752,779]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
<taxonomicName id="C5D4A8B5A81FD70DB7B0FD4F3AE6704C" box="[200,469,752,778]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Hyacinthella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pallasiana">
<emphasis id="30A00F24A81FD70DB7B0FD4F3AE6704C" box="[200,469,752,778]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Hyacinthella pallasiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
par 
<bibRefCitation id="6645AEC7A81FD70DB57CFD4F3996704D" author="Stepanenko O. V. &amp; Popov G. V." box="[516,677,752,779]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" pagination="40 - 43" refId="ref4919" refString="Stepanenko O. V. &amp; Popov G. V. 1997. On the immature stages biology of Merodon nigritarsis Rondani, 1845 (Diptera: Syrphidae). The Karkov Entomological Society Gazette 5: 40 - 43." type="journal article" year="1997">Stepanenko &amp;</bibRefCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="026BD336A81FD70DB7B0FCAC3F6970F2" blockId="5.[200,1183,446,949]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
Popov (1997). La larve semble, en effet, se nourrir sur des plantes à bulbe. Quatorze indi- vidus ont été capturés à Bernex indiquant la proximité d’une population de cette espèce. Fait intéressant si l’on considère qu’une seule espèce de plante à grand bulbe a été observée dans les alentours (N. Delabays comm. pers.): 
<emphasis id="30A00F24A81FD70DB580FCC638DB70D4" box="[760,1000,889,914]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
<taxonomicName id="C5D4A8B5A81FD70DB580FCC638D770D4" box="[760,996,889,914]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Muscari" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="racemosum">Muscari racemosum</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Une association entre 
<taxonomicName id="C5D4A8B5A81FD70DB67FFC253AD870F2" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1845" box="[263,491,922,948]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigritarsis">
<emphasis id="30A00F24A81FD70DB67FFC253AD870F2" box="[263,491,922,948]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Merodon nigritarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
et 
<taxonomicName id="C5D4A8B5A81FD70DB575FC2439C670F2" box="[525,757,923,948]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Muscari" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="racemosum">
<emphasis id="30A00F24A81FD70DB575FC2439C670F2" box="[525,757,923,948]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Muscari racemosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
semble donc être très probable.
</paragraph>
